{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "profile-identities-e2e",
    "name": "Profile – GET /me/identities",
    "description": "E2E tests for GET /api/v1/profile/me/identities.\n\nFolders:\n  1. setup          — register → verify-email → login (stores idents_access_token)\n  2. happy-path     — assert response shape; empty array for a fresh user (no OAuth links)\n  3. auth-guard     — no token / tampered token → 401\n  4. rate-limiting  — exhaust ident:ip: (20 slots) → 21st → 429\n\nNotes:\n  • T-01 / T-03 (≥1 identity, order ASC) require a linked OAuth account.\n    These are verified at the store-integration level (store_test.go) and will be\n    confirmed end-to-end once the Google / Telegram OAuth E2E collections (Group D)\n    run before this collection and seed identity rows for idents_email.\n  • T-04 / T-05 (access_token / refresh_token_provider absent) are structural\n    properties of the SQL query and response type; their absence is also checked\n    in the happy-path request below.\n\nRun `make _e2e-db-clean` and `make _e2e-kv-clean` before this collection.\nRequires TRUSTED_PROXIES=127.0.0.1/32 in .env.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "const n = (pm.collectionVariables.get('_req_seq') | 0) + 1;",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_req_seq', n);",
          "const ip = '10.'+((n>>16)&0xff)+'.'+((n>>8)&0xff)+'.'+(n&0xff);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', ip);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "setup",
      "description": "Register, verify email (via Gmail API), and log in to obtain an access token for identities tests.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /register → 201",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const email = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email');",
                  "if (!email) { console.error('[ERROR] gmail_test_email not set'); }",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('idents_email', email);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('idents_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "// Gmail OTP fetch",
                  "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
                  "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set'); return; }",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for verification email...');",
                  "const start = Date.now(); while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
                  "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Verify your\" newer_than:1h');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({url:'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q='+query+'&maxResults=3',method:'GET',header:{Authorization:'Bearer '+token}},(err,res)=>{",
                  "    if(err||res.code===401){console.error('[ERROR] Gmail list failed');return;}",
                  "    const msgs=res.json().messages;",
                  "    if(!msgs||!msgs.length){console.warn('[WARN] No email found');return;}",
                  "    pm.sendRequest({url:'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/'+msgs[0].id+'?format=full',method:'GET',header:{Authorization:'Bearer '+token}},(e2,r2)=>{",
                  "        if(e2){console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed');return;}",
                  "        const msg=r2.json(); let body='';",
                  "        const parts=msg.payload&&msg.payload.parts;",
                  "        if(parts&&parts.length){const p=parts.find(x=>x.mimeType==='text/plain')||parts.find(x=>x.mimeType==='text/html');if(p&&p.body&&p.body.data)body=atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g,'+').replace(/_/g,'/'))}",
                  "        else if(msg.payload&&msg.payload.body&&msg.payload.body.data)body=atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g,'+').replace(/_/g,'/'));",
                  "        if(!body){console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode body');return;}",
                  "        const match=body.match(/(?<!#)\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
                  "        if(!match){console.warn('[WARN] No OTP found');return;}",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('idents_code', match[1]);",
                  "        console.log('[INFO] OTP stored:', match[1]);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"display_name\":\"IdentsUser\",\"email\":\"{{idents_email}}\",\"password\":\"{{idents_password}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /verify-email → 200",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const code = pm.collectionVariables.get('idents_code');",
                  "if (!code) { console.error('[ERROR] OTP not set — Gmail fetch did not complete. Check gmail_access_token and --delay-request >= 8000.'); }"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"email\":\"{{idents_email}}\",\"code\":\"{{idents_code}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/verify-email",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "verify-email"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /login → 200 (store access_token)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(body.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('idents_access_token', body.access_token);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"identifier\":\"{{idents_email}}\",\"password\":\"{{idents_password}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "happy-path",
      "description": "Exercises GET /me/identities for a freshly registered user who has no linked OAuth accounts.\n\nWhy E2E:\n  • D-01 (empty list → 200 with array, never null) — requires a real DB round-trip; sqlc\n    :many returns nil for empty result sets and the store must coerce that to a non-nil slice.\n  • D-03 (access_token absent) / D-05 (no audit row) — structural checks on the live response.\n\nNot covered here (unit / integration tests):\n  • T-01 (≥1 identity) / T-03 (order ASC) — require a seeded OAuth identity row;\n    covered by store_test.go and will be exercised after OAuth E2E flows (Group D) run.\n  • T-06 (nullable fields omit)  — handler_test.go TestHandler_Identities/nullable_fields_omitted_when_nil\n  • T-08 (service error → 500)   — handler_test.go TestHandler_Identities/service_error_returns_500",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /me/identities → 200 (empty array, sensitive fields absent)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// T-02: fresh user has no linked identities — must return 200 with empty array (D-01)",
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('Content-Type is application/json', () => pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/json'));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "// D-01: identities key must be present and be an array, never null or absent",
                  "pm.test('identities key is present', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('identities'));",
                  "pm.test('identities is an array', () => pm.expect(body.identities).to.be.an('array'));",
                  "pm.test('identities is empty for a fresh user (D-04)', () => pm.expect(body.identities).to.have.lengthOf(0));",
                  "",
                  "// D-03: provider credential columns must never appear in any response",
                  "pm.test('access_token absent from response body (D-03)', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(JSON.stringify(body)).to.not.include('access_token');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('refresh_token_provider absent from response body (D-03)', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(JSON.stringify(body)).to.not.include('refresh_token_provider');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{idents_access_token}}"
              },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/profile/me/identities",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "profile", "me", "identities"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "auth-guard",
      "description": "T-07: Verifies that the JWT middleware rejects requests with no token or a tampered token.\nThese checks exercise the real chi middleware stack end-to-end.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /me/identities (no Authorization header) → 401",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
                  "pm.test('code is unauthorized', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('missing_token'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/profile/me/identities",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "profile", "me", "identities"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /me/identities (tampered Bearer token) → 401",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));",
                  "pm.test('code is unauthorized', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('invalid_token'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer not.a.real.jwt" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/profile/me/identities",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "profile", "me", "identities"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "rate-limiting",
      "description": "ident:ip: limiter — burst=20, rate=20/1min (0.333 t/s).\nAll warmup requests use the valid access_token from setup (JWT auth fires before the\nlimiter inside the JWT middleware group). 26th request → 429 too_many_requests.\n\nRetry-After = ceil(1 / (20/60)) = ceil(3.0) = 3 seconds.\n\nWhy 25 warmup requests instead of 20:\n  The ident:ip: limiter is a token bucket (rate=20/60≈0.333 tok/sec). During the warmup\n  phase Redis response latency means the 20 requests can take 2–6 seconds total, refilling\n  up to ~2 tokens. Without extra drain requests the 21st fires into a non-empty bucket and\n  returns 200 instead of 429, causing an intermittent flaky failure. Sending 5 additional\n  drain requests (slots 21–25) absorbs up to ~15 seconds of refill (5/0.333=15s), making\n  the test deterministic on any machine/network speed.\n\nRequires Redis flushed (make _e2e-kv-clean) before this folder.",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": ["pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', '127.0.0.1');"]
          }
        }
      ],
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "warmup 1/20 — consume ident:ip: slot (→ not 429)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('not rate-limited yet (ident:ip: slot 1/20)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.not.eql(429));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
